    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n503" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀλεγεινός</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄλγος</span>), comp. neut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄλγιον</span>, sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄλγιστος</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">painful, hard, toilsome;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πυγμαχίη, κύ̄ματα, μαχλο-</span>
          
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σύνη</span>, ‘fraught with trouble,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 24.30</span></i>; freq. w. inf., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἡμίονος ἀλγίστη δαμάσασθαι</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.655</span></i>.—Adv. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄλγιον</span>, used in exclamations, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τῷ δ᾽
            ἄλγιον</span>, ‘so much the worse’ for him!</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
